 Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England"},"en":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–1629","28 February 1575":"28 February 1575","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1542":"1542","1530":"1530","1596":"1596","1570":"1570","1629":"1629","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Chute, Wiltshire, England":"Chute, Wiltshire, England","St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bartelmew","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: from the genitive form, <i>Bartholomaei</i>, of the Latin personal name <i>Bartholomaeus</i> (see   Bartholomew  ). This surname is very rare in Germany. In part, it is a Gottscheerish (i.e. Gottschee German) surname, originating from the Kočevsko region in Lower Carniola, Slovenia (see   Kocevar  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Bartholomew","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Bertilmew</i>, <i>Bertelmy</i>, a borrowing of the Old French form of the Biblical personal name <i>Bartholomew</i> (from Latin <i>Bartholomaeus</i>; Hebrew ‘son of Talmai’, said to mean ‘having many furrows’, i.e. rich in land). This was an extremely popular personal name in Christian Europe, with many vernacular derivatives. It derived its popularity from the apostle Saint Bartholomew (Matthew 10:3), who was, among other things, the patron saint of tanners, vintners, and butlers.","As an Irish name, it has been used as an Anglicized form of <b>Mac Pharthaláin</b> (see   McFarlane  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Bartelmew was born in 1530, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Alys Cordray in 1570, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1596, in his hometown, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–1629","28 February 1575":"28. veebruar 1575","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1542":"1542","1530":"1530","1596":"1596","1570":"1570","1629":"1629","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chute, Wiltshire, England":"Chute, Wiltshire, England","St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–1629","28 February 1575":"28. helmikuuta 1575","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1542":"1542","1530":"1530","1596":"1596","1570":"1570","1629":"1629","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chute, Wiltshire, England":"Chute, Wiltshire, England","St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England"},"fr":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–1629","28 February 1575":"28 février 1575","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1542":"1542","1530":"1530","1596":"1596","1570":"1570","1629":"1629","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Chute, Wiltshire, England":"Chute, Wiltshire, Angleterre","St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Bartelmew est né en 1530, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé Alys Cordray en 1570, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1596, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 66 ans."},"de":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–1629","28 February 1575":"28. Februar 1575","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1542":"1542","1530":"1530","1596":"1596","1570":"1570","1629":"1629","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Chute, Wiltshire, England":"Chute, Wiltshire, England","St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England","lifeSummary":"Thomas Bartelmew wurde 1530 in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hat 1570 in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom Alys Cordray geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1596 im Alter von 66 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–1629","28 February 1575":"28 February 1575","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1542":"1542","1530":"1530","1596":"1596","1570":"1570","1629":"1629","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angletè, United Kingdom","Chute, Wiltshire, England":"Chute, Wiltshire, England","St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Angletè, United Kingdom","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England"},"hu":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–1629","28 February 1575":"1575. február 28.","1577":"1577","1575":"1575","1542":"1542","1530":"1530","1596":"1596","1570":"1570","1629":"1629","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Anglia, United Kingdom","Chute, Wiltshire, England":"Chute, Wiltshire, England","St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Anglia, United Kingdom","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England"},"id":{"1530–1596":"1530–1596","1542–1577":"1542–1577","1575–1629":"1575–16